description:
1866 - graduated University of Edinburgh with MB CM with honours; 
1867 - house physician at Edinburgh infirmary; 
1868 - published thesis on digitalis and awarded MD; studied pharmacology and physioloigcal chemistry in Vienna, Berlin, Amsterdam and Leipzig with Willy Kuhne and Carl Ludwig; 
1870 - lecturer in materia medica and pharmacology at Middlesex Hospital; 
1871 - lecturer in materia medica and pharmacology at St Bartholomew’s Hospital; development of experimental pharmacology; 
1874 - elected Fellow of Royal Society; 
1900 - knighted; 
1908 - baronetcy

